## **Standard three-target workflow (verified June 2026)**

Replace `CONTAINER_ID` with `docker ps` Postgres container ID (e.g. `143972c3c40c`).

### **1. Local Docker â€” full export + import**

Runs steps 0â€“7: `pg_dump` â†’ reorder â†’ PROD SQL copy â†’ patch â†’ schema â†’ import (renumbered dev file) â†’ sequence sync.

```powershell
F:\project_workspace\application-deployments\documentation\database_export_import\batch_files\database_export_import_refresh.bat F:\project_workspace CONTAINER_ID /FORCE
```

Equivalent using mosc-temp path:

```powershell
F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\code_html_template\batch_files\database_export_import_refresh.bat F:\project_workspace CONTAINER_ID /FORCE
```

**Import file (local, no `/PROD`):** `mosc-temp\code_html_template\SQLS\sequence_fix_inserts\corrected_event_media_inserts.renumbered.sql` (low local IDs).

### **2. VPC dev RDS â€” reuse prepared SQL**

Requires `mosc-temp\.env.local` â†’ **dev** host (`event-site-manager-dev-postgres.cwffi3ch4r75.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com`).

`/REMOTE` auto-enables `/PROD` â†’ imports `corrected_event_media_inserts.ordered_PROD.sql`.

```powershell
cmd /c "echo PRODUCTION| F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\code_html_template\batch_files\database_export_import_refresh.bat F:\project_workspace /SKIP-EXPORT /REMOTE /FORCE"
```

### **3. VPC prod RDS â€” reuse prepared SQL**

`.env.local` normally points at **dev**. For **prod**, temporarily swap RDS settings, run import, **restore dev settings**.

```powershell
# 1) Backup .env.local
Copy-Item F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\.env.local F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\.env.local.dev-backup-import -Force

# 2) Set prod RDS_ENDPOINT / DB_* from Secrets Manager (do not commit passwords)
$secretJson = aws secretsmanager get-secret-value --secret-id "event-site-manager/prod/rds/postgres" --region us-east-1 --query SecretString --output text | ConvertFrom-Json
# Update RDS_ENDPOINT, DB_USERNAME, DB_PASSWORD, DB_NAME in .env.local (PowerShell line replace)

# 3) Import
cmd /c "echo PRODUCTION| F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\code_html_template\batch_files\database_export_import_refresh.bat F:\project_workspace /SKIP-EXPORT /REMOTE /FORCE"

# 4) Restore dev .env.local
Copy-Item F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\.env.local.dev-backup-import F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\.env.local -Force
Remove-Item F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp\.env.local.dev-backup-import -Force
```

**Alternative:** Rename `.env.local` temporarily and create `code_html_template/batch_files/database_target.local.env` from [database_target.local.env.example](mdc:documentation/database_export_import/batch_files/database_target.local.env.example) with prod host (batch reads fallback only when `.env.local` is missing).

